  "prompt": "What are the best places to stay in munnar?",
  "response": "Munnar, a picturesque hill station in Kerala, India, is known for its lush tea plantations, misty hills, and serene lakes. Here are some of the best places to stay in Munnar, catering to different budgets and preferences:\n\n### Luxury Resorts and Boutique Hotels:\n1. **The Leaf Munnar**  \n   - A luxurious eco-friendly resort offering stunning views of tea plantations, with modern amenities and wellness facilities like Ayurvedic spa treatments.\n\n2. **Chandy's Windy Woods**  \n   - A luxury boutique resort surrounded by tea gardens, offering spacious rooms, a pool, and personalized services.\n\n3. **Fragrant Nature Munnar**  \n   - Known for its panoramic views, this resort combines luxury with nature and offers activities like guided plantation walks and birdwatching.\n\n4. **Blanket Hotel & Spa**  \n   - A unique boutique hotel on a tea estate, offering a blend of colonial charm and modern comfort, with a spa and infinity pool.\n\n### Mid-Range Hotels and Resorts:\n5. **The Leaf Munnar (Riverdale)**  \n   - A mid-range option by The Leaf group, offering cozy rooms, beautiful views, and a peaceful ambiance.\n\n6. **Devonshire Greens Leisure Hotel**  \n   - A family-friendly resort with spacious cottages, a pool, and a restaurant that serves delicious local cuisine.\n\n7. **T&U Leisure Hotels**  \n   - Known for its serene location and moderate pricing, this hotel offers comfortable rooms and excellent hospitality.\n\n8. **Elysium Gardens Hill Resort**  \n   - A charming resort with beautiful gardens, affordable room options, and a relaxing atmosphere.\n\n### Budget Stays and Homestays:\n9. **Green View Munnar**  \n   - A budget-friendly homestay offering clean and comfortable rooms with beautiful views and warm hospitality.\n\n10. **Royal Retreat Munnar**  \n    - A budget resort located near the town center, offering good facilities at economical rates.\n\n11. **Munnar Tea County by KTDC**  \n    - A government-run property that offers affordable lodging with basic amenities and a scenic location.\n\n12. **Dream Catcher Homestay**  \n    - A cozy and affordable homestay with personalized service, ideal for budget travelers.\n\n### Unique Stays:\n13. **Camp Noel**  \n    - A glamping experience in Munnar, offering luxury tents surrounded by nature.\n\n14. **Tea Valley Resort**  \n    - Located in the heart of tea plantations, this resort offers a unique blend of comfort and nature.\n\n15. **Tea Harvester**  \n    - A themed homestay where guests can experience the life of tea plantation workers, complete with guided tours and activities.\n\n### Tips for Choosing Accommodation:\n- **Location**: Choose a stay close to the town center if you want easy access to shops and restaurants, or opt for a secluded spot for tranquility.\n- **Season**: Book well in advance during peak tourist seasons (October\u2013May) to secure the best options.\n- **Activities**: Some resorts offer plantation tours, trekking, and cultural experiences; choose based on your interests.\n\nMunnar has something for everyone, whether you're looking for luxury, a mid-range stay, or a budget-friendly option!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
